text:
👥so you have romantic relationships- short or long, happy or sad - or the worst - happy then sad! ***
but the relationships that carry you through are friendships.  who do you call when he/she comes into your life? your girls. who is there if he leaves or you leave him? your girls. and who is there when he stays? who is there when your parents are sick, or on that
dreadful day when they will pass?who is there to hold you to your truth, and listen to your confessions and dreams and the craptastic times you compromised? who can bond over everything from gods to shopping, from makeup to political debates, from the tedious ins & outs of being a woman to the overarching dharma of the female incarnation?? yah guessed it: yah girls. 👯‍♀️👯‍♀️👯‍♀️
hold them close - they are your longest  relationships, and your lasting family. all love and thanks to mine for carrying me through so many tricky times! when i revealed myself to be flawed, you revealed yourself to be my friends.😘

text:
here’s a little art to go with your saturday morning (afternoon?) coffee ☕️ ~
.
today we’re bringing you the minimalistic gold silhouettes of adriana lopez, aka @speakinsmoke, from her series “all that glitters is fools gold”.
.
.
of her series, she says “in bogota, colombia, one of the most prominent museums, the museo del oro, is home to the largest collection of gold artifacts in the world. these artifacts serve as a glimpse into the indigenous communities that lived in present day colombia before the spaniards colonized the region. as a an american born colombian i am only now starting to learn about the deep cultural significance gold had to the indigenous communities that my family come from. in my work i aim to reflect and connect with the indigenous community who’s traditions initiated the myth of el dorado. i aim to become the gold covered chieftain famously depicted in the museum’s most prized artifact by repeatedly depicting my image and the images of those closest to me in gold leaf.”
.
.
enjoy! let us know what you think in the comments below 👇
.
.
images (in order): “ando sola”, “dime amigo”, “me encanta esta chaqueta”, “los trillos” and “no veo bien”. all work by @speakinsmoke.
.
.
.
.

text: #metoo ✊🏾in 2006, tarana burke was consumed by a desire to do something about the sexual violence she saw in her community. she took out a piece of paper, wrote "me too" across the top and laid out an action plan for a movement centered on the power of empathy between survivors. more than a decade later, she reflects on what has since become a global movement -- and makes a powerful call to dismantle the power and privilege that are building blocks of sexual violence. "we owe future generations nothing less than a world free of sexual violence," she says. "i believe we can build that world." @taranajaneen did her first ever @ted at an official ted conference and you can watch it in full (link in bio ☝🏾) #metoomovement #strongwomen #strongblackwomen @tedx_official

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
viol & séquestration, projet réalisé le 3 nov. avec @orfeas_gotronakis . s'il a été salué... en même temps le projet a fait polémique... je comprends que sans explication, le risque est de laisser libre cours aux dérives de la pensée qui a horreur du vide...
sachez que c'est une vraie démarche où, moi même je me suis laissée mettre en scène dans des scènes violentes, parfois dégradante, alors que je suis habituellement une personne pudique. mais quand orfeas m'a parlé qu'il souhaite dénoncer ce qu'il a subi, et lever le voile sur ces scènes qui seront pour certaines victimes, un écho perpétuel dans leur intime abîmé, alors j'ai réalisé que son point de vue était une façon de capter votre âme plus que vos yeux. ce sont des sujets graves où tout le monde est unanime et pourtant cela reste tabou ! j'y vais en pleine conscience, en tant que victime attouchée, sachez-le !
3 clichés issus de sa page insta du 5 novembre :
- libérer une parole de victimes,
- montrer la violence ressentie par ces victimes,
- exorciser cette violence.

ce post est pour introduire les 5 prochains thèmes évoquant le viol & la séquestration :
- des chiffres sur la violence faite à  autrui et choix d'élargir au delà du viol .
- la notion du "care" : paradigme qui a changé la vision du prendre soin, et qui pour moi est une notion qui manque cruellement dans notre apprentissage .
- les fantasmes : on en parle beaucoup surtout pour les réaliser, mais mesure-t-on les risques ? c'est une notion qui me pose question et je vais l'évoquer.
- le off du projet pour montrer l'ambiance dans laquelle nous étions : gaie et enjouée et responsables sur un sujet grave.
- des témoignages et la notion de résilience : je ne suis pas thérapeute mais je suis une oreille et une main attentives à entendre pour écrire en mon nom ce que je glane d'une parole... trop long...temps... tue... .
liste n°écoute nationale, anonyme, gratuit pour les victimes :
- le 119 : maltraitance enfant/adolescent  7j/7j h24
- urgences france le 17 (112 europe) ou 114 personnes sourdes.
- le 0 800 05 95 95 : contre le viol des femmes (cfcv.asso.fr) lundi au vendredi de 10h à 19h.
- le 39 19 : violences conjugales femme & hommes

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
photo with @otherbill who graciously opened his home to kick off my new favorite weekend of the year! 🤸🏻‍♀️
the austin acro seasonals are finally here! and i’m super grateful to get to be a part of planning something so huge and fun and wonderful as the seasonals. 
today i’ll be holding space for something very important to me, something i have helped develop into fruition over the past few months with inspiration and collaboration from our women’s acro groups and girltalk acrochats - today we’ll be partnering with safeaustin.org to build an interactive discussion surrounding consent, boundaries, power dynamics, and sexual harassment in acro communities; about how to recognize violations of consent, and how to effectively respond and support those being violated. in the #metoo era, this is such an important concept to grasp and skill to learn, especially for those who wish to be leaders of their communities or teachers to those new to the practice. i’m especially grateful we could do this during the seasonals where we’ll have 5 different acro cities represented and in attendance. our main goal for this was so that we could collectively set the standard in our communities and beyond for dealing with these types of issues, and to get on the same page about how so very important consent and communication really are. some may claim that acro is just a fun sport or hobby, but there’s an undeniable sense of community that surrounds it, and as the saying goes in our community: we keep each other safe, and we help each other grow. 💗 @acroyogaaustin

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: this ninth statistic in celebration of 200 #herstaircasescenes, ends this special series on a serious note. i am sure that the #metoo movement has escaped absolutely none of you, it surely did not escape the 213 women featured on here. at least 20 of them (8,0%), have explicitly spoken out about their experiences with various types of sexual harassment and assault, since the weinstein story broke. this includes - among others - tippi hedren, who was open about her experiences on set with hitchcock long before #metoo and has recalled her experiences in the past year, and a number of weinstein's most famous accusers, such as gwyneth paltrow and uma thurman. it excludes a great group of actors that did not live in a time where they might have felt supported enough to share their stories too, as well as a group of contemporaries that may still not be ready to share their horrible experiences with the world now. important steps have been taken in this past year, here's to the hope that many more will be taken soon!
name: Her Staircase Scene
tweet_full: this ninth statistic in celebration of 200 #herstaircasescenes, ends this special series on a serious note. i am sure that the #metoo movement has escaped absolutely none of you, it surely did not escape the 213 women featured on here. at least 20 of them (8,0%), have explicitly spoken out about their experiences with various types of sexual harassment and assault, since the weinstein story broke. this includes - among others - tippi hedren, who was open about her experiences on set with hitchcock long before #metoo and has recalled her experiences in the past year, and a number of weinstein's most famous accusers, such as gwyneth paltrow and uma thurman. it excludes a great group of actors that did not live in a time where they might have felt supported enough to share their stories too, as well as a group of contemporaries that may still not be ready to share their horrible experiences with the world now. important steps have been taken in this past year, here's to the hope that many more will be taken soon!

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: if you know me you know some things about me. first of all. this is my season. my time of year. second, i want every kid to have a happy christmas//kwanzaa//hanukkah season. our family will help as many as we can but i’d also like to ask you to do the same. if you’re reading this, find a kid. any kid. and help them have a better holiday. it doesn’t take a ton of money or even effort. it just takes a genuine desire to love and help. compassion helps kids of all ages learn about social interface. builds positive neural pathways. this doesn’t need to be a #metoo thing. just be cool to a kid and maybe you and that child are the only people that will ever know. but that matters little. #istillhearthebells #becooltokids

⭐️

text:
.
i’ve been reading ta nehisi coates, 
so forgive me, 
if i’m altogether lacking the language
for this particular inequity,
been busy trying to resolve
white supremacy.
but i’ve been listening 
to the burden of this body 
that bears the wounds 
of deprivation of basic safety.
.
learning, 
it’s a worthwhile battle
to use your voice,
words,
you don’t think you have, 
you don’t think suite you,
or think you’re allowed.
.
so, in #thepursuitofbravery
& @johnlucask
thank you
for something that i could only,
as of yet, 
write at the request of someone - 
else and of your kind.
.
in solidarity
with the ally (@modernmogli)
the perpetrator,
& everyone in between; 
me. too.
.
it wasn’t what i thought it would be
because i couldn’t think it into being anything
just turned up the music loud enough
to have the cops called on myself
and allowed it to breathe
right through me,
write me out
so
.
you can carry it for awhile
.
i’m not your sacrifice.
.
..
.
without further ado:
..
i might need security.
@ sumofelzbieta.com
.

text:
after sharing my story in my last post, i hope you continue to read especially if you yourself are a survivor of a sexual assault. ❤️
i did not tell really anyone until about 5 years later...i dealt with so much guilt, shame, hatred, heartache, attachment issues, trust issues, insecurities, anxiety, ptsd, and so many other things. i felt the loss of control, the feeling that i was worth nothing, i had a damaged body that would never be the same. 
i didn’t realize how strong i had become even though i felt weak. when i finally told my mother and friends, i felt empowered to seek help, and to fight back by helping others who were survivors as well. so listen to me now.. to the survivor - you are not alone! you are strong, beautiful, and so brave. it is not your fault! you have the power to help others. silent survivors trust me you are not alone...i was there and it took a long time for me to get here. the healing process takes time and you should take all the time you need. don’t give up on yourself. those survivors that chose to speak out...thank you. you are so brave, and are a voice for those who aren’t ready to share theirs yet. you are speaking out and standing up for all of us...and could be saving the persons life next to you. lastly, for those who have a survivor in their life and have not experienced this type of trauma personally...please just listen - believe them, be supportive, love them, remind them they are worthy and beautiful - be that light.

text:
привет!
сегодня  день пробуждения мужской энергии. 24 лунный день. символ дня - #медведь.
💡
удачное время для интрижек, интимной близости и зачатия ребенка. супружеские отношения наполняются теплотой. рекомендуются нагрузки на мышцы, тренировки, активное участие в мероприятиях. сегодня у вас может открыться второе дыхание, вы можете почувствовать, как в вас возрастает физическая мощь, пробуждаются новые силы. употребите их на созидательные процессы.
💡
день удачен для всех активных и целеустремленных людей. можно начинать новые дела и обсуждать текущие. день хорош для финансовых операций и торговли.  все будет удаваться, если вы приложите усилия. луна также благоволит творческим людям. с успехом пройдут концерты, выставки, показы, спектакли. не ленитесь, используйте всю энергию для осуществления каких-либо дел. чем больше успеете сегодня, тем лучше. слабым и неуверенным в себе людям лучше остаться дома или отправиться на природу, чтобы отдохнуть.
⠀
благо❤дарю
#медведь #луна #лунныйкалендарь #мужчина #family #love #you #metoo #отношения #кризис #moon #вечер

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
jak powinna wyglądać skrzywdzona osoba, żebyś jej uwierzył?
może chodzić po telewizjach?

what should the victim look like to be believed?
can she go to tv?

katarzyna dziedzic: ,,pod zdjęciami piszą, że kłamię, bo chcę się wybić na krzywdzie byłego partnera. ich główny zarzut – "gdyby naprawdę cię pobił, nie chodziłabyś po telewizjach, tylko płakała w domu". powiem ci szczerze, że właśnie to chodzenie po telewizjach mnie uratowało. po pobiciu nastąpiły najgorsze dwa tygodnie mojego życia – wcześniej miałam wizję mieszkania w gdańsku, układania tam sobie życia z miłoszem, wzięłam nawet kredyt i w jednej chwili wszystko się rozpadło. zostałam zupełnie sama, musiałam wrócić do olsztyna, mieszkać u brata… to był horror i właśnie dzięki temu, że nie miałam czasu się załamywać, bo ciągle dostawałam wiadomości, umawiałam się na wywiady, czułam się potrzebna innym kobietom… właśnie dlatego się nie poddałam i staram się od nowa ułożyć sobie życie". (https://kobieta.wp.pl/ruszyla-sprawa-milosza-p-to-jest-gra-na-czas-6322524358441089a)

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
@regran_ed from @warif_ng -  day 7 | december 01
world aids day

during sexual assault that involves  penetrative sex, women are exposed to infections as perpetrators do not typically use any forms of contraception such as condoms. this leads to a higher incidence of hiv/aids cases.

if untested, women run the risk of spreading this infection to others and if untreated, can lead to death.

the use of post- exposure prophylaxis (p.e.p) treatment of hiv with the appropriate drugs within 72 hours of the assault reduces the risk of infection.  this treatment is available at the warif centre - free of charge.

if you are a survivor of sexual violence or rape, visit the warif centre or a medical facility within 72 hours to get tested and treated, to reduce your risk of the hiv /aids infection.

warif cares. world aids day

#repost @warif_ng (@get_repost)
・・・
day 7 | december 01
world aids day

during sexual assault that involve  penetrative sex, women are exposed to infections as perpetrators do not typically use any forms of contraception such as condoms. this leads to a higher incidence of hiv/aids cases.

if untested, women run the risk of spreading this infection to others and if untreated, can lead to death.

the use of post- exposure prophylaxis (p.e.p) treatment of hiv with the appropriate drugs within 72 hours of the assault reduces the risk of infection.  this treatment is available at the warif centre - free of charge.

if you are a survivor of sexual violence or rape, visit the warif centre or a medical facility within 72 hours to get tested and treated, to reduce your risk of the hiv /aids infection.

warif cares. world aids day

share our stories , repost , tag someone and join us in the #orangetheworldwithwarif campaign as we participate in the #16daysofactivism against gender based violence.

text_retweet:
#repost from @soar_institute 
#d17 community event @judsonchurchnyc ! 
please rsvp using this link: bit.ly/d17nyc2018 ✨✨✨ rp 
on december 17 at judson memorial church, we remember sex workers who have died from violence. international day to end violence against sex workers was founded 15 years ago in san francisco by @anniesprinkle as a memorial and candlelight vigil for the victims of the seattle green river killer. the day calls attention to hate crimes committed against sex workers worldwide, as well as the need to remove the stigma, discrimination and indifference that contributes to violence against them. it is now observed globally in local vigils and gatherings. 
you are welcome to participate in part or all of the evening’s events:

5pm -- the candle inscription and community-building session begins

7pm -- the open mic begins; reading of names, stories, songs, poetry and performances are encouraged.

9pm -- clean-up promptly begins

let us know if you want to be on the program and/or have relevant announcements, names and stories for us to honor and uplift on that day. 
more details about the #nyc vigil are on our facebook page: 
http://bit.ly/dec17nyc2018

details about other global events are available at www.december17.org 
veronica vera @missveronicavera
doctor of human sexuality

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
+++ day 1 of 24 days of intersectional feminism +++
.
last year, i explained in my first post why i'd prefer to speak of 'sexualized violence' instead of 'sexual violence' (swipe to read the full caption of last year's post).
.
a couple of months ago though i read an article that changed my mind on this topic again. it suggested that we should differentiate between sexual and sexualized violence due to the intentions of the abuser.
.
of course power always plays an important part in cases of sexual(ized) violence. but the demonstration of power is not always the motivation of the abuser. i would say that quite often the sexual satisfaction of the abuser is what motivates them.
.
obviously, speaking of a sexual act when not everyone involved has consented is quite problematic. but i think emphasizing that there are different kinds of intentions abusers have is really important.
.
what are your thoughts about that?
.

text_retweet:
glad första december allihop! 🌲❄ i denna djungel av advents- och julkalendrar av olika slag, tänkte jag köra en repris på förra årets #vågaväljajulkalender och ser gärna att ni som kan och vill hänger på! dela med er av texter på dagens tema som ni ser i första bilden, förklaringar på luckornas tema finner ni om ni bläddrar bland bilderna. tagga @vagavalja i bilden och avsluta med #vågaväljajulkalender ❤❄ då advent infaller på andra datum i år än förra året, så byter vi helt enkelt bara plats på advetsluckan och luckan innan. .

jag kommer att reposta en del av förra årets inlägg och blanda med nya texter. .
lucka 1: #metoo
.
ett år av #metoo och allt som kommit därav. samtyckeslagen. kulturprofilen blev dömd i tingsrätten. utbildningssatsningar kring sexuellt våld sker över hela landet. fler och fler anmäler. allt fler organiserar sig och kämpar för jämställdhet. jag har fått möjlighet att föreläsa och utbilda båda unga och vuxna om det sexuella våldet och dess konsekvenser. jag och @briljanta.tillsammans har arrangerat manifestationer och festivaler för att uppmärksamma #metoo och stå upp för oss och alla andra som överlevt sexuellt våld. i en relativt liten stad son kalmar blir en snabbt igenkänd om ens ansikte pryder ett tidningsomslag eller syns i artiklar i alla lokala tidningar. det har varit en ära att få vara en förkämpe och ett ansikte utåt för överlevare av sexuellt våld. men det är också påfrestande, att i så många sammanhang vara en person som blivit våldtagen. inte bara alexandra. inte bara socionom, skolkurator, sambo eller faster. våldtäktsoffer. våldtäktsöverlevare. #metoo öppnade upp för en gemenskap jag tidigare saknat, där jag kunde dela erfarenheter med andra och inse att jag inte är ensam, men det öppnade också en dörr som jag inte tycks kunna stänga, utan alltid lämnar lite på glänt. mina trauman ligger inte längre begravda i mitt innersta, de sitter i huden, alldeles ytligt och hela tiden närvarande. det kan göra mig både glad och ledsen. men oavsett hur smärtsamt det varit, är jag oerhört tacksam för det här året. det har gett mig styrka i all min trasighet. vi skapar historia. glöm aldrig det. #vågaväljajulkalender

text:
we spend much of our day and time focused on others. we are nurturers. but we are also our own unique self.  it is okay to invest in ourselves - whether it is our own private time, a new book, something pretty, a coach, taking a class, getting our degree, or whatever it is that is something we’ve dreamed of and know would add value for us. 
the only permission we need to ask is of ourselves.  it is okay to invest in us. 💜

text:
at just 13 years old, she was already working as a prostitute in her village inside a small suburb of nairobi, kenya. we all sat in a circle inside a tiny community center as a group of ten women and girls shared their stories of how rape, poverty, and a lack of opportunity forced them onto the streets as sex workers.

one girl explained to us how a local villager once told her to think of her body as a supermarket — plenty to offer people for the right price.

their stories leave you feeling incredibly angry at humanity and, yet, in awe of it when you realize how someone so young can be so strong.

over the past year, all ten women and girls have been able to leave prostitution with the help of @freelyinhope, a nonprofit that offers scholarships, free mental health services, and leadership training to survivors of sexual violence in kenya and zambia.

the program, that aims to get young girls off the streets, is called “malkia,” that’s swahili for “queens.” the girls are clearly grateful for the possibility and opportunity to live a better life, but the thought of it all is still overwhelming — a complicated and foreign feeling that is equally delightful and daunting.  before enrolling in the program, some of the girls didn’t understand the concept of setting goals. their counselors had to literally define the words and even explain what it means to dream. 
we asked one girl what she now hopes to do in the future. “catering,” she said. she then rested her head into her lap and started crying uncontrollably. . . . . . . . . . . . 
#kenya
#africa
#nairobi
#metoo
#timesup

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
day 7 | december 01
world aids day

during sexual assault that involves  penetrative sex, women are exposed to infections as perpetrators do not typically use any forms of contraception such as condoms. this leads to a higher incidence of hiv/aids cases.

if untested, women run the risk of spreading this infection to others and if untreated, can lead to death.

the use of post- exposure prophylaxis (p.e.p) treatment of hiv with the appropriate drugs within 72 hours of the assault reduces the risk of infection.  this treatment is available at the warif centre - free of charge.

if you are a survivor of sexual violence or rape, visit the warif centre or a medical facility within 72 hours to get tested and treated, to reduce your risk of the hiv /aids infection.

warif cares. world aids day

share our stories , repost , tag someone and join us in the #orangetheworldwithwarif campaign as we participate in the #16daysofactivism against gender based violence.

text:
there is a problem with feminism. its purpose was to give women equal legal rights. but it’s morphed into something quite different. there is no denying of the injustice and violence towards women. it’s intolerable and deplorable! 
as women we need to stop whining and own our feminine. what we should demand is respect. 
i’ve blamed patriarchy. i’ve wallowed in self pity. i’ve allowed myself to suffer through depression for years. and i’m simply tired of the feminist narrative that plays over and over again in my head. it was counterproductive to my feminine...... my true authentic self. i had to grow the fuck up. biologically men and women are different! #fact  and that determines our emotions, thoughts and behaviors. instead of accepting the beauty and the miracle of the feminine i’ve denied its endless creative power, nurturing power and potential. #wakeup
men and woman are essential to the balance. the man as the protector and warrior and the woman as the creator and nurturer. •asl notebooks, 2016
@asleninde

text:
i'm going to do something a little different today. i read a disgusting post comparing women like elizabeth taylor to more "demure" actresses of the time in a very derogatory way. 
so i wanted to clarify a few things.

liz was sexualized from childhood. she grew up with peope only noticing her looks and ignoring everything else. she was pushed into child stardom by her parents who took her to hollywood and left her to her own devices.
what do we now know happens to pretty girls left unchecked with predatory older men? this is several decades before #metoo. nobody would have protected her.

yes she married 8 times. like most women who were ignored by their parents and abused by authority figures she craved love. sadly she never got to learn how to have it in a healthy way.
her first husband beat her on their wedding night so she filed for annulment. in fact, despite her desire to be loved she never allowed a man to dominate her.
she made terrible decisions where men were concerned out of a desperation for acceptance.

she seemed to show a healthier love for her friends. by all accounts she was fiercely loyal to those she loved. she was also a devoted mother, showering her children with the love and support she never had.

she was far more intelligent than she gets credit for. the final few decades of her life she ran several successful perfume and beauty lines. 
she had balls too. she campaigned to educate the public about hiv/aids in the 80s and would always stand for what she believed was right.

so, she was someone who loved extremely hard but not always in a healthy way. 
she was never taught personal responsibility so she figured that out through trial and error in the public eye.
she was treated as though her beauty was all she had to offer and had to fight to be taken seriously.

i'm tired of people writing shit that tears her to shreds just because she wasn't their idea of "ladylike".
she did the best with what she had and i respect and admire her for it.

rant finished.

#womeninhistory #badasswomen  #womeniadmire #elizabethtaylor
#feminist #feminism #doublestandards
#shedidherbest #quitbeingdicks #nobodysperfect #feminismisforeverybody #notjustforworthy
name: Abbie-Jayne Shilling

#gprepost,#reposter,#notetag @mariacarrasco via @repostapp ======> @mariacarrasco:#blackdot #puntonegro el símbolo en contra de la violencia ⚫️✋🏼 si ves esto, significa: “soy víctima de violencia, necesito ayuda y no puedo hablar” ⚫️✋🏼 hoy, 25 de noviembre, en el día internacional para terminar la violencia hacia las mujeres (y que da inicio a 16 días de activismo), publica una foto de tu mano con este símbolo  para ayudarnos a difundir su significado y a generar conciencia entre tu comunidad #spreadtheword #hearmetoo 🖤 en soutien aux femmes victimes de violences...

gender biases can blinds us in the predominant sex-trafficking narrative when we imagine only female victims and male perpetrators. but boys comprise about 50 percent of sexually exploited children, according to a 2008 study done by john jay college of criminal justice.
.
to create blinded, i literally wore a blindfold while splattering paint onto the canvases. our cultural blinders make it difficult for vulnerable male victims to reveal their souls to expose nefarious activity.
.
blinded seeks to uncover the truth and help heal both female—and male—survivors.

text:
have you ever found yourself slipping down into the comparisons wheel? looking on your social media feeds, all the people around you and comparing your life to theirs? well i have and it’s an awful feeling that eats you up inside. thoughts of thinking you aren’t enough, that people don’t care about you, you are alone, no one loves you, you should be a huge success by his point in your life, why haven’t you been able to find a relationship that works out....i could go on and on. does anyone else relate to these feelings? 
the lesson i have learned is to take one day at a time. don’t apologize for not being there yet. honour yourself. give yourself time to heal, to work though the challenges. have you heard that the same challenges will continue to repeat themselves until you learn that lesson????? so true! 
know that you are enough. you are the most important person and no one else is like you. you are love. it’s time to start treating yourself like you want to be treated. give to you. take all the time you need. don’t listen to people telling you this and that. take the time to look within, focus on what you need, what you want and then one day at a time take a baby step. 
that stuff on social media is a highlight real-trust me in this. we just don’t post the shitty stuff because we want people to think we are awesome and have everything going on in life. no one is perfect. no one has this life. stop the social media scroll if you’re finding yourself getting back into the comparison wheel. take a break. delete your apps for a while. it will be challenging at first, but trust me-you will live through it. 💕 .
.
.
📷: pinterest

have you ever found yourself slipping down into the comparisons wheel? looking on your social media feeds, all the people around you and comparing your life to theirs? well i have and it’s an awful feeling that eats you up inside. thoughts of thinking you aren’t enough, that people don’t care about you, you are alone, no one loves you, you should be a huge success by his point in your life, why haven’t you been able to find a relationship that works out....i could go on and on. does anyone else relate to these feelings? 
the lesson i have learned is to take one day at a time. don’t apologize for not being there yet. honour yourself. give yourself time to heal, to work though the challenges. have you heard that the same challenges will continue to repeat themselves until you learn that lesson????? so true! 
know that you are enough. you are the most important person and no one else is like you. you are love. it’s time to start treating yourself like you want to be treated. give to you. take all the time you need. don’t listen to people telling you this and that. take the time to look within, focus on what you need, what you want and then one day at a time take a baby step. 
that stuff on social media is a highlight real-trust me in this. we just don’t post the shitty stuff because we want people to think we are awesome and have everything going on in life. no one is perfect. no one has this life. stop the social media scroll if you’re finding yourself getting back into the comparison wheel. take a break. delete your apps for a while. it will be challenging at first, but trust me-you will live through it. 💕 .
.
.
📷: pinterest

text:
h a p p y b i r t h d a y
.
soul birthing hat #geburtstag.
.
heute vor einem jahr ist mein zweites #baby geboren. ich habe mich getraut meiner #inneren stimme und #herzensweg zu folgen und mein wirken & wissen voll und ganz auf die #werdendenmama und #geburt auszurichten.
.
zu diesem schönen anlass erkläre ich dir kurz, was sich hinter #soulbirthing verbirgt ♡
.
🤰ganzheitlicher geburtsvorbereitungskurs ➡️ hier lernst du alles zum thema #hypnobirthing, #schmerzarme und #selbstbestimmte geburt. du lernst tolle mentaltechniken, lernst super effiziente methoden um dich selbst in die totale entspannung und vertrauen zu bringen!
alles mit oder ohne partner - ganz wie du es wünschst.
.
🤱doula ➡️
als deine #doula (griech. dienerin der frau) begleite ich dich auf dem aufregenden und schönen weg von der schwangerschaft über die geburt bis ins wochenbett! ich weiche bei der geburt nicht von deiner seite und unterstütze dich #vertrauensvoll #mutmachend #beschützend und #menschlich!
.
🏋️‍♀️aufarbeitung schwerer geburten ➡️
dies ist für dich, wenn du mit deinem geburtserlebnis einfach noch nicht im frieden sein darfst. wenn die gedanken an das geschehene dich nicht #loslassen oder du gar ein #trauma erlebt hast.
als psychologin verfüge ich über viele wertvolle und erstaunlich einfach anzuwendende techniken um dir und deinem #baby den start ins #leben wieder leichter zu machen.
weil du es darfst!!!
.
melde dich gern bei mir wenn eines dieser themen dich betrifft!
.
ich bin unendlich #dankbar für jede #mama die es möglich macht diesem tollen #herzenstraum nachzugehen.
.
.

text: they got bill, but not neil too..🤦🏿‍♂️ buzzfeed 11/30/18 - fox broadcasting company and national geographic are investigating astrophysicist and cosmos host neil degrasse tyson after three women came forward with allegations of sexual misconduct. tchiya amet, a woman who attended graduate school with tyson, wrote in 2014 about an encounter that she said left her traumatized for decades. amet said she was friends with tyson in the 1980s at university of texas at austin, and was at his apartment when he offered her something to drink. she said he drugged and raped her. katelyn allers, an associate professor at bucknell university, told mcafee that she'd met degrasse tyson at an after-party of an american astronomical society event in 2009. she approached him to take a photo, and he complimented a tattoo that spanned her collar-bone, back, and shoulder — then grabbed her and reached into her dress to see it better. ashley watson told patheos she worked as tyson's assistant and quit after several instances of sexual harassment, including a sexual advance and sexual comments. text:
shaming is a form of mental and emotional abuse. shame is an intense and painful response to failure, whether real or perceived.  shame creates a barrier to vulnerability.  it is the creation of the masks that so many of us wear on a daily basis to avoid access to our hearts.  without vulnerability we cannot access our authentic selves.  our souls are looking for a place to call home, and shame says "no room in the inn." this is one word that i would like to remove from our modern vernacular.  it keeps people in abusive relationships; unproductive jobs; self-deprecating situations, and suicidal spaces. shame is that feeling that makes you want to hide or even die.  we all make mistakes. don't compare your non-fiction to the fairytales people post on social media.  you are enough, no matter what mistakes you've made.  h.u.g.g.s (healing, understanding, guidance & growth w/simone)

text:
il y a quasi un an pile, au sein du collectif #ouvretesailes, j'ai créé une performance cabaret autour du mouvement #metoo et de la libération de la parole des femmes. avec les quatre comédiennes qui ont accepté de travailler avec moi, on a livré nos véritables témoignages. cette performance est devenue un court-métrage « cabaret cochon », tournage organisé en à peine quelques semaines, réalisé en une journée seulement avec @saraginac et une équipe magnifique. 11 comédiens, une choré, de la fumée et bien sûr.. des masques de cochon. 
le film est arrivé finaliste au @nikonfr film festival, 8è sur 1640 films, on a pu l'admirer sur le grand écran au mk2 bibliothèque, on était fiers.  il a également été coup de coeur du #shortfilmcorner du @festivaldecannes, et grâce au formidable journaliste de @brutofficiel @charlesvillaa, même si nous étions une goutte dans l'océan des films du festival, même si j'avais le soleil dans les yeux, j'ai pu prendre la parole au nom du cochon. aujourd'hui, ce n'est pas, mais vraiment pas encore gagné, mais je me réjouis chaque jour que la situation des femmes et la considération de nos droits évolue, que notre parole continue à se libérer, et que des initiatives comme #noustoutes rassemblent tant de femmes et d'hommes. 
aujourd’hui notre cochon est en compétition et en projection aujourd'hui à paris pour le prix du public au festival libre emois, un festival mettant en avant "une certaine vision de la liberté et de la diversité". nos groins frétillent de joie ! 🐷🐽🐖🎬 www.libresemois.com/festival

#cochonunjourcochontoujours #gratitude #cinema #shortmovie #woman #womansrights

text:
alla stazione radiofonica con base a cleveland, ohio, wdok christmas 102.1, un ascoltatore, avrebbe richiesto all’emittente statunitense di eliminare dalla sua playlist il celebre brano, scritto da frank loesser nel 1944, “baby, it’s cold outside”, ampiamente riproposto in ogni dove nel periodo natalizio per i suoi riferimenti alla stagione più fredda dell’anno. “è una scelta dei nostri ascoltatori”, ha motivato desiray di wdok, spiegando come – riporta fox – dopo la segnalazione dell’ascoltatore l’emittente avrebbe proposto un sondaggio sul suo sito web a proposito del brano e la maggioranza dei votanti avrebbe deciso di non trasmetterlo. 
la stessa persona ha raccontato a fox che la richiesta di mettere da parte il classico natalizio sarebbe legata al movimento di matrice femminista #metoo, nato dopo lo scandalo legato alla figura del magnate hollywoodiano hervey weinsteinlo scorso anno: “la gente potrebbe dire ‘ne abbiamo abbastanza del #metoo’, ma se davvero metti da parte questo e ascolti il testo, non è qualcosa che vorrei per mia figlia il trovarsi in quella situazione”. concludendo: “il brano può essere attraente, ma cerchiamo forse di non promuovere quel tipo di idea”. il pezzo, che è stato riproposto nel corso degli anni nelle versioni di innumerevoli artisti, include strofe quali “non posso restare” (voce femminile): “ma tesoro fuori fa freddo” (voce maschile). ma anche: “dimmi cosa c’è nel drink” (voce femminile): “la risposta è no” (voce maschile).
#ellafitzgerald
#metoo

text:
sharing my love and compassion in regards to the #metoo movement to my other selves who are on the other side of the movement.

beginning with myself for the times i might have expressed my sexuality in ways that felt offensive, hurtful and traumatizing in anyway. i forgive and love meee. ♥️ and to all of my brothers and sisters who have felt so disconnected from source that they expressed their creative life force ~ sexuality in ways that are not in alignment with the truth of their being. i want you to know that you too are deeply loved for you are a part of me. you too are unconditionally loved by source exactly as you are and i’m so sorry for what unfolded in your life that made you believe you don’t belong or that you are not loved. i see you. i accept you. i love you. may you remember your power. may you forgive yourself. may you liberate yourself from shame and guilt and let your heart rest free in this ocean of love from where we came from and where we are immersed now. ♥️ i realize that many of you here might be new to my page and might not know that a few years ago, i openly shared my experience with sexual trauma, my healing process and how i feel that this was sincerely one of the best catalysts accelerating my growth and awakening. today i stand stronger than ever, still feel i haven’t been a victim of anyone and know in my core that even as a small child i created that experience for myself. 
i believe i never shared my own perspective on this movement and i’ll say this lovingly and respectfully... discernment!! as much as i acknowledge pain, violence and trauma i don’t believe perpetuating the victim, perpetrator, separation mentality is the way to end sexual assault!! we can only heal our planet by remembering and educating ourselves on universal principles, completely owning our power, realizing that we are one thus removing ourselves and others from this old blaming game. all lives matter. when we stand up for one and fight, reject others we are rejecting ourselves. 
love on ♥️

text:
tedxplacedesnationswomen је јединствен догађај, који oкупља људе око "идеје вредне ширења", у виду кратких, упечатљивих говора и перформанси. овогодишње издање - "empower" - ће се фокусирати на оснаживање жена и родну равноправност. једанаест инспиративних и страствених говорника који покривајући широки спектар питања као што су нуклеарно разоружање, права радника на радном месту, стицање дигиталних вештина и женско генитално мучење (фгм), скупиће се како би се појачале следеће идеје: • уједињене нације и друге међународне организације у женеви имају огроман трансформативни и позитиван утицај на живот људи широм света, сваког дана. • 2018, са креираним покретима #metoo и #timesup, постала је важна година за оснаживање жена. • када су жене оснажене, оне чине велике ствари за своје заједнице и друштво у целини. • без обзира на то да ли су предузетници, лекари, политичари, историчари или студенти, сви су изузетан фактор промена. догађај пружа јединствену поставку за прославу женских разлика у свету, јуче, данас и сутра. • најочитији изазови нашег времена могу се решити када су њихови таленти и идеје откључани.

надамо се да ће моћне успешне приче наших говорника да надахну публику да се ангажује!

#tedxnations @tedxpdnwomen @ungeneva 
уживо у четвртак 6. децембра од 15:30h - 19:00h,
конференцијска сала правног факултета, видимо се! 
@pravnifakultetubg

text:
logging back into this account after 5 years was a bit crazy.  i deleted the few followers i had, unfollowed all the accounts i'd been following, and put my account as private. my intention was to track my journey and become public again once i had results that i was proud of.  but as i've started following people on their weight loss journeys, it's not just their results that i find inspiring, but their thoughts and struggles as well.

my side by side photos (before and after seems like the wrong terminology) are a bit different than others.  i was small for the majority of my life, and it is only in the last couple years that i've struggled with unhealthy weight. 
in 2013 i weighed 130lbs.  by 2015 i was up to 150lbs (bigger, but still healthy). 2015 was also the year i was assaulted.  that experience led to rapid weight gain.  in 2017 i was 200lbs, and knew i needed to change.  i joined ww and was down to 175lbs in 2 months!!! and it was easy-- better choices and portion control, and the weight was falling off.  i started receiving compliments on my appearance, and i suddenly retreated back to old habits.  the weight had become my armour, and by losing it i was exposing myself and becoming more vulnerable.  i put back on all the weight, plus 20lbs.

today in 2018 i'm 220lbs.  i'm ready to try again.  this time i know i can't just focus on  diet and exercise.  i'm working on overcoming those psychological barriers that have been holding me captive.  because weight is never just about food--- it's tied up with all of your emotions and experiences. 
summary: i'm on a physical and mental health journey :) #health #fitnessjourney #sidebyside #anxiety #depression #metoo #goals #workinprogress

what does a women need to be? she can be angry, be intelligent, be witty, be interesting, be funny, be adventurous, be talented, be the one that has fire in her eyes and knows what she wants, be the one who makes things before others can imagine them by becoming a dreamer, be the one who has thirst for knowledge and become a thinker, be the one that perseveres... there are an eternity of things a woman can be. she is her own definition of amazing. we are blessed to be in a country where women are encouraged to be their true selves. that’s were all the power comes from. 
happy bahraini women’s day!

text:
on se marre mais la cause qu’on défend fait rire personne , on pose comme des andouilles stephane et moi pour défendre l’initiative de tristane . #avecelles car les violences faites aux femmes concernent tout le monde . 
moi même lourdement embêtée par les hommes dans la rue , moi même violentée et malheureusement aussi agressée je n’ai pas réagit sur le mouvement #metoo pour des raisons qui me regardent .
 cependant adhérer à un mouvement ou  les hommes et femmes s’unissent pour que ça s’arrête est à ce jour là moindre des choses . 
ma fille mérite de grandir sans craintes du sexe opposé ,  mon fils mérite de grandir dans un monde ou son genre n’est pas une excuse pour opprimer l’autre. 
in english : no more violences against women it’s too last century ❤️

text:
@rollerderbyerfurt hat mit #mehralsbeine eine wichtige aktion gestartet, um gegen die häufig sexistische und einseitige darstellung von frauen im öffentlichen raum zu protestieren. auslöser sind die debatten um die werbemaßnahmen zweier thüringer damen-volleyball-teams. in ihrem aufruf stellen #rollerderbyerfurt ein paar wichtige punkte klar:
**
leider zeichnet sich unsere gesellschaft nicht durch ein gleichgestelltes, diverses frauenbild aus. frauen dienen in der werbung oft als symbolträgerinnen für schönheit, zartheit oder verletzlichkeit, worüber beworbene produkte, oft in keinem sinnhaften zusammenhang, verkauft werden sollen. so begegnen uns im öffentlichen raum überproportional häufig schlanke, weiße frauen, die meistens nichts anderes tun, als schöne bekleidung zu tragen, schön geschminkt zu sein und schön zu lächeln. das ist ein baustein dessen, was wir als sexismus verstehen.
**
den ganzen aufruf findet ihr hier: 
https://rollerderbyerfurt.wordpress.com/2018/11/28/statement-zur-werbung-erfurts-laengste-beine/

unterstützen könnt ihr die aktion, indem ihr selbst ein bild von euch bei (im weitesten sinne) sport mit dem hashtag #mehralsbeine postet.

#nosexism #girlpower #feminismrocks #feminism #stillneedingfeminism #metoo #aufschrei #werbung #sport #stark #frauen #nichtnurschön #thüringen #frauenbild #divers #vielfältg #gleichstellung #gleichberechtigung #sexismus #showthemforwhattheyare #thisgirlcan #strongwoman #wandern #wandernistauchanstrengend #berge #draußen #nofilter

طفلی بچس دیگه هنوز بلد نیست یه دوره فشرده بیاد یادش بدیم چجوری این کارا رو بکنه اینطوری همه چیو بهم نریزه آقای روحانی ما هم بهش چند روز پیش گفت حاضریم بهت کمک کنیم هیچیم ازت نمی خوایم . مثلا #بختیار کسی چیزی گفت اصلا تونست چیزی بگه. اونم تو فرانسه اصل دموکراسی یا #فروهر و خیلی دیگه .
آره پسر جان این جور کار ها فوت و فن داره آره بابایی اره گل پسر حرف گوش کن

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

through regular meets, leaders can also build trust among victims to speak up, use the whistle blowing channel, and reach the organisation’s internal complaints committee (icc) board members. .

text:
16 days of the year, we dedicate ourselves to 16 days of activism against women and child abuse.
.

don't keep quiet. don't allow it. women are worth so much in the world. we are breaking barries. we are where we've never been before. and yet, some women choose to ignore abuse inflicted by others to their friends, family, neighbors or colleagues.
.

emotional abuse is just as bad as physical abuse. i am still recovering after being silent for 10 years, and away from the abuse for 6 years. something nobody talks about. it's taboo. no one wants to believe that a partner (who in their eyes is so great) but a monster behind closed doors, can be capable of breaking every single thread of my being into pieces. i loved, i forgave, i hoped. i waited for change. i accepted apologies over and over again. i thought i would never be good enough for anybody. i kept up appearances. smiled, but felt like i was dying inside. i believed all the insults. i was broken down to nothing. i wanted to take my own life. i prayed not to wake up in the morning, every night. i fought with god and all the beings that i could think of. i pushed my family and friends away. i had nothing but my daughter. .
she is my angel. my saviour. the only reason i survived. and the only reason i had the strength to walk away.
.

please, i am appealing to my women followers (and men). let's start helping and supporting each other. stop judging. you know, the lady at work that has such "bad mood swings". the b*tch at work with rbf etc. those are the ones most probably hiding behind the anger. or hiding behind a smile. just try to be nice even if it kills you. because you never know what's happening behind closed doors.

#womenempowerment #16daysofactivism #womenabuse #childabuse #support #lovingcircle #joinhands #stopabuse #dontkeepquiet #nolongeravictim #mystory #metoo #strongwomen

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
nella vita ciò che conta è mettere passione in ciò che fai. se dedichi tutta te stessa e fai qualcosa che ami, vedrai i risultati. 
la mia più grande soddisfazione è proporre alle persone a cui tengo un’azienda fidata, proporre loro dei prodotti di qualità a un prezzo contenuto, proporre loro un’azienda che opera nel rispetto dell’ambiente.
sono contenta di non deludere mai la fiducia che viene riposta in me, ma alla fine quando fai qualcosa con amore i risultati non possono che essere positivi.❤️

text:
"everyday i battle with the thought of the day when i finally figure out if my dad is my dad.

i am 24yrs old and i still jump from relationship to relationship with men that are twice my age simply because i have daddy issues. being with them makes me feel better about my self, i am confident and have mastered the art of manipulating these men. they don't believe my age first of all and i make sure i never let them know my story.

my dad rejected a three month embryo simply because my mum had walked out before she knew she was expecting me. she only returned to him because he promised to be a better husband.

all my life i have been envious of my own siblings yet they were innocent. our dad made it his life mission to treat us all different and for me the scars i got were verbal. he made sure he insulted me and my mum at every chance he got, he ensured that i felt his bitterness in every stance. 
when it comes to my mum, she isn't different. i thought i would trust her because we were always at war with the same man, i thought she would become my best friend through it all until she broke my heart and trust.

mine is a cycle where i have to deal with trust issues, broken relationships that i don't want to mend.

i am in my room and i want to cry but i have become so empty that even tears fail me. inside i am actually crying but there is no teardrop to evidence this.

i was sexually abused in my fathers house for years by a relative, from the age of 9. at 14 when i spoke up because i was starting to realize that what was being done to me was wrong, my own dad called me a slut and blamed the occurrences on my mum 😨😨😨 my mum confided in her friends who later spread word of my shame and my entire neighborhood found out, i will never forget this even if i have forgiven.

i can go on and on.

but guess what, in all this; i have found god who battles with me everyday to remind me of my worth and how much he loves me.

i have a support group where we are free to be ourselves and share with each other, that to me is a step further into my healing." - anonymous. 
the writer asked to be kept anonymous.

text:
autumn 
autumn settles in my heavy heart
wine mingles with a thousand feelings
farewells are as many as fallen leaves in this season
with your hand clutched at my heart
i need you to remember our unspoken promise

i do not fear longing
but your sorrow haunts me
we have but the wind to blame for our parting

i do not fear longing
but your loneliness haunts me
no one will hear our desolation
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
.
“the only keeper of your happiness is you. stop giving people power to control your smile, your worth and your attitude.” 🙏🏻
.
i used to be in a relationship where i was mistreated physically and emotionally.
.
i had to delete my facebook and all guy friends’ numbers, throw all the “slutty” dresses, had to send the pictures and video call him to let him know who i was with and where i was....
.
he was too jealous that we couldn’t even watch the movie together or go for a date without fighting as he always compared himself with other guys and asked me questions like who looked better etc...
.
we were fighting, crying and physically hurting each other everyday.
.
all my best friends and family hated  him and told me to leave him but i used to think he was the only person in the world who could love me like this.
.
i thought all these jealousy and possessive behaviours were because he loved me so much.
.
although i used to judge a girl being in such relationship to be stupid, when you are actually loving someone it is really hard to leave such relationship as you hope that they will change for us.
.
this is the biggest mistake we could make as the only thing we could change in this world is ourselves.🙏🏻
.
we cannot forse anyone to change themselves.
.
that’s why we always need to remember that we deserve much better than this and the only person actually can help you and make you happy is yourself.
.
after i realised this i started to go to gym and train to be physically and mentally stronger. training definitely helped me a lot to transform into a stronger version of myself.💪🏼
.
you can do it. i believe in you. now it’s time for you to believe in yourself.🙌🏻
.
make a declaration that today starts the healing process. from now on, you will work toward living the amazing life you deserve.❤️
.
also please remember that there are people who can help you at women’s legal service qld, dv connect, our watch, lifeline etc. !!! .
izzy & i will be sharing more of our experiences for the next #16days for #hearmetoo #orangetheworld .⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
if you have experienced any abusive relationships or any assaults let’s speak up & tag us / use #empowerourwomentoday 🌈🙏🏻⁣⁣⁣
⁣

text:
devenir invisible. ces mots ne sont pas de moi. ils sont d’une femme qui tous les matins avant de partir travailler s’habille pour faire disparaître sa féminité . 
l’habillement au travail. quand on est une femme, ce sujet est loin d’être anodin. une jupe jugée trop courte ou un décolletée trop plongeant et vous voilà cataloguée incompétente. pourtant avant ce soir, j’espérais que la situation avait évolué et qu’aujourd’hui une femme pouvait être féminine et compétente même dans un environnement professionnel dit masculin. que ses habits n’étaient ni un handicap, ni un frein, ni une raison de s’excuser. je me suis trompée . aujourd’hui, les femmes aussi compétentes et intelligentes soient elles, doivent encore adapter et penser à leurs tenues avant d’aller au travail . pour éviter les regards, les remarques et les gestes déplacés. ce soir, cette femme s’est confiée et malgré son sourire et sa résiliation, j’ai senti sa peine. il y a des mots, des gestes, des regards qui marquent. une femme pour laquelle j’ai beaucoup d’admiration car malgré les atteintes elle est toujours là. fidèle, loyale et professionnelle. 
on dit qu’il n’y a ni métier d’homme ni de femmes et que l’habit ne fait pas le moine . alors pourquoi les femmes devraient s’enlaidir  ou se rendre invisible quand elle sont entourées d’hommes ? pourquoi des talons ou du maquillage leur ôte automatiquement toute intelligence et compétence? ce soir, c’était la dernière soirée @poll_et_mera .une soirée avec beaucoup d’échange et de confidences.  ce soir, je suis reconnaissante et heureuse d’avoir échangé avec toutes ces femmes. je suis heureuse d’avoir ri. et je vais me focaliser là dessus. sur le positif. sur la persévérance de cette femme, sur la bienveillance et sur les sourires des autres. #femmesupport #soireebodypositive #mamansuisse #instamaman #feminisme #switzerland #thereseandthekids #confianceensoi #humeur #vendredi #bodypositive #metoo #smile #citation #quotesoftheday #bobmarley

text:
looking forward to reading @100womeniknow. from their website: “the project began with a questionnaire given to 100 young women, asking them about their experiences of rape and sexual assault. the results give a blunt, honest, unapologetic and emotional account of the realities that women face. the research led 100 women i know founder, phoebe montague, to direct and produce an award-winning short documentary film comprised of intimate interviews with four rape survivors. when approached by break the habit press, a new independent publisher, the 100 women i know book was born. this is a movement with a mission to strengthen solidarity between survivors and initiate open conversation about sexual violence. phoebe has now joined forces with jazmin, one of the women featured in the documentary, together they are launching sister organisation people we know. an organisation providing an educational programme with the aim of preventing young people from becoming victims or perpetrators of sexual violence. they plan to tour the film, book and accompanying workshop programme to schools, colleges and community projects. these transformative workshops are designed to educate and engage young people and encourage participants to reconsider their preconceived ideas, judgments and misconceptions surrounding sex, relationships and sexual violence. 
young people are the future and it is our responsibility, as a society, to empower them with tools for change.”
pictured here is @jazziesirius from the project. 
#100womeniknow #bookstagram #feminist #feminism #metoo #timesup

looking forward to reading  from their website: “the project began with a questionnaire given to 100 young women, asking them about their experiences of rape and sexual assault. the results give a blunt, honest, unapologetic and emotional account of the realities that women face. the research led 100 women i know founder, phoebe montague, to direct and produce an award-winning sho documentary film comprised of intimate interviews with four rape survivors. when approached by break the habit press, a new independent publisher, the 100 women i know book was born. this is a movement with a mission to strengthen solidarity between survivors and initiate open conversation about sexual violence. phoebe has now joined forces with jazmin, one of the women featured in the documentary, together they are launching sister organisation people we know. an organisation providing an educational programme with the aim of preventing young people from becoming victims or perpetrators of sexual violence. they plan to tour the film, book and accompanying workshop programme to schools, colleges and community projects. these transformative workshops are designed to educate and engage young people and encourage paicipants to reconsider their preconceived ideas, judgments and misconceptions surrounding sex, relationships and sexual violence. 
young people are the future and it is our responsibility, as a society, to empower them with tools for change.”

text:
well, how come you only want tomorrow?
with its promise of something hard to do
a real-life adventure
worth more than pieces of gold
blue skies above, sun on your arms
strength in your stride and hope
in those squeaky-clean eyes

you'll get chilly receptions
everywhere you go
blinded with desire
i guess the season is on

so you train by shadow boxing
search for the truth
but it's all, but it's all used up
break open your million-dollar weapon
and push your luck
still you push, still you push your luck
a broken-nosed mogul are you
one of the new-wave boys

same old thing in brand, new drag
comes sweeping into view

as ugly as a teenage millionaire
pretending it's a whizz-kid world
you'll take me aside, and say

well, david, what shall i do?
they wait for me in the hallway
i'll say, don't ask me, i don't know any hallways
but they move in numbers
and they've got me in a corner
i feel like a group of one
no, no, they can't do this to me

i'm not some piece of teenage wildlife

those midwives to history
put on their bloody robes
and the word is that the hunted
one is out there on his own

and you're alone
for maybe the last time
and you breathe for a long time
then you howl like a wolf
in a trap and you daren't look behind

you fall to the ground
like a leaf from a tree
and look up, one time
at that vast blue sky
scream out of line
as they shoot you down

no, no, i'm not a piece of teenage wildlife

i'm not a piece of teenage wildlife

and no one will have seen
and no one will confess
the fingerprints will prove
that you couldn't pass the test
there'll be others on the line
filing past, who'll whisper low
i miss you, he really had to go
well, each to his own
he was another piece of teenage wildlife 
another piece of teenage wildlife
another piece of teenage wild

text:
repris: jag betraktar mina hundar. hur han hoppar upp på hennes rygg och juckar. hur hon fräser ifrån nå så grymt. och jaha. vad vill jag ha sagt med det. jo: en liten reflektion från mitt eget liv. bland grisgubbar. jo. förstår ni. grisgubbar råkade jag ut för som ung, sprudlande, nyfiken, livsbejakande tonåring. nyfiket på väg mot vuxenlivet. de såg min sprudlande ungdomlighet som någon sorts invit. något som väckte deras lust. begär. till mig. (historierna finns här på insta under hashtaggen #grisgubbar). fast de var oerhört många år äldre än mig så tyckte de att vi skulle "ha i hop det". nåja. det om detta. det jag vill berätta om och som jag vet att så många känner igen sig i är detta: jag var en jävel på att krångla mig ur dessa obehagliga situationer, komma därifrån med oskulden i behåll. kränkt men lättad att det inte slutade värre. men vad jag också lyckades med, som 14åring, 15åring, 16åring....jo, det var att jag såg till att dessa äckliga män också kom ur situationen. med hedern i behåll!!! var i hela friden hade jag lärt mig att detta var viktigt??? att de inte skulle känna sig bortgjorda? att det inte skulle bli obekvämt? jag var en fena på detta. helt sjukt!!! jag önskar att någon lärt mig att vråla högt å tydligt. att få hela sällskapets blickar riktade mot mig och oss där jag bara skriker ut "lägg av din jävel"!!!! få alla att fatta vad som händer. se. förstå. precis så som bolla gör. 
#metoo #allavi
